  <text>
    <body>
      <div>
        <p><seg type="diplomatic" subtype="address">Norman, sheriff of Berwick, to all his men of Corstorphine, <seg type="diplomatic" subtype="salutation">Greeting</seg>:</seg> <seg type="diplomatic" subtype="disposition">Know that I have granted and given in perpetual alms to Holyrood in Edinburgh
                  and to the abbot, and to the brethren serving God there, my
                  Chapel at Corstorphine with all revenues belonging to the
                  same chapel.</seg> <seg type="diplomatic" subtype="witnesses">As witnesses, Henry the Earl, and Edward the Chancellor, and Thurald the
                  Archdeacon of Lothian, and Richard the Clerk of Edinburgh.</seg> At Berwick.</p>
      </div>
    </body>
